      "content": "but that feels so hollow. local efforts aren't going to stop the oceans from rising or the ecosystems from collapsing. it's like trying to put out a forest fire with a water pistol. it just feels exhausting to keep performing these tiny little tasks for a future that isn't even going to happen. i can't shake the feeling that fighting it is just a way to prolong the inevitable suffering.",
